    List of supported primitive types. Transactional objects can only reference other transactional objects, or the following primitive types. ObjectFabric sees those primitives as immutable, i.e. changes made to an instance would not be replicated or persisted. Most of those types are already made immutable by Java's type system, like String, but others are not, like byte[]. If you modify a byte[] in on process, updates will not be replicated to other processes.
